1
2
3
4
5
ðŸ”¹ 3. until Loop

i=1
until [ $i -gt 5 ]
do
  echo $i
  ((i++))
done
Explanation:

Starts with i = 1.

Runs the loop until the condition becomes true.

Here, it continues until $i becomes greater than 5.

